{"word":"μυθέομαι","slug":"μυθέομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>μυθέομαι</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:μῦθος'><el>μῦθος</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to say, speak</i>, <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> et <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to say that</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>: <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> only, <i>to order</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to tell, recount</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; also, <i>to tell of</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> cogn. <i>to say, speak, utter</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>; <el>πόλιν μ. πολύχρυσον</el> <i>to speak</i> of the city as rich in gold, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to say over to oneself, con over, consider</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}